    "# Consumer Credit Underwriting Industry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Overview"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Most known as FICO, our credit score was supposedly created to tell institutions how a certain individual manages their personal finance or how well they \"deal with money\" so that these institutions can make credit-related decisions on the possibilities of the individual repaying the loan on time. The FICO score given will determine the financial risk of the individual that will influence the accessibility and cost for him/her to borrow money of finance a purchase. Therefore, heavily impacting his ability to grow financially and acquire new assets. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "That being said, one would think that the consumer credit rating industry is a fair and well distributed landscape with many players and access to everyone. Yet, it's one of the heaviest concentrated industries where only 3 credit bureaus control over 90% of the market. With the industry in the hands of Equifax, TransUnion and Experian, there is doubts whether they use all information available or only the ones that they will easily have access to in a low cost operation. \n",
    "\n",
    "Highly concentrated industries, such as the consumer credit rating, is where millions of dollars are spent in research and development but no disprution is created, mainly because the 3 main players have no reason to disrupt an industry that they have perfectly divided among them and can control or profit from it the way it suits them best. This landscape although has a high barrier for new entrants creates a perfect landscape for Fintechs to enter through the back door. In this case study we will analyze how one fintech startup is doing it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![alt text](myfico.png \"SOURCE\")"
   ]
