   "source": [
    "## The Fintech Startup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> \"What autopilot is for an airplane, a decision engine can be for a lender.\" "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Source: https://lendingfront.com/blog/industry/underwriting-the-new-underwriting-technology-evaluating-innovations-in-data-use-and-credit-decisioning/"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### *ZEST AI*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Founded in May 2009 by Douglas Merrill, a former Google CIO and VP of Engineering, Zest AI came from an idea to use Google-like algorithms to make consumer credit more transparent, available to more people and significantly less expensive. In 2020, the startup reached close to 200 employees and has already received 217 million dollars in funding from venture firms such as Baidu, Fortress Investment Group (SoftBank) and the Founders Fund, which has Peter Thiel as partner."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Zest AI role in the fintech industry is to help big borrowers to basically have more loan approvals,therefore increasing revenue, without adding more risk to the institutions' portfolio. By using data scrapping to feed machine learning models Zest is able to include more data and sophisticated math to reduce loan's default rates signficantly of portfolios. With such tool in hand, the startup focuses on large players in the banking and borrowing industry tapping into a market that reached its record high of $138 billion dollars borrowed last year. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The solution powered by Zest AI is unique due to the company's ability to provide the full set of services required for a lending decision on an application. It's an unfair advantage to compare the ZEST AI solution that follows each compliance policy to the cost and time an institution would have to spend to create such solutions. The chart below illustrates the complex parts of the decision process."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![alt text](solution.png \"SOURCE\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###### Image Source: https://www.zest.ai/solutions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### *The technology behind*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "According to Zest AI's website, the startup enables lenders across the globe to deploy powerful, compliant credit models siwftly and easily in suite that is able to scrap and categorize data, output a decision and be compliant with the enourmous amount of policies that regulate consumer lending. How does this technology works?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ensembled machine learning models is the answer. For Zest AI more specifically, Deep Stacking. Such model, uses a non linear ensemble function to take both the data and the model scores as its own inputs to produce a decision. As the model builds submodels before processing in a single neural network, it allows the tool to select the correct balance to weight the decision in each submodel according to specific variables set by the financial institution. The unique setup of Zest AI's deep stacking allows the company to uncover deep relationships between these submodels which learns when to apply each submodel based on its strengths.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![alt text](deepstacking.png \"SOURCE\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###### Source: https://www.zest.ai/article/many-heads-are-better-than-one-making-the-case-for-ensemble-learning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As any other AI model, deep stacking also has its challenges. But ZEST AI instead of having these challenges as a setback it uses to leverage the startup's business model and sell it's product. \n",
    "The three main challenges ensembled models like deep stacking have are: \n",
    "\n",
    "**Engineering Complexity**: even with a very well funded team of developers, a financial instituion would take years to break through such complexity in techinical dependencies, runtime and model verification. \n",
    "\n",
    "**Explainability**: most models will explain to you what its driving the score but ZEST AI is able to provide an explanation for a model-based decision. \n",
    "\n",
    "**Compliance**: the enourms amount of scrutiny these decisions goes through to comply with consumer lending regulatory laws is absurd and ZEST AI automates a large part of this process."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The technologies mentioned above constitute the product that ZEST AI sells, which is called ZAML, Zest Automated Machine Learning platform. The product is sold with an emphasis in three components that we reviewed and are summarized below: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![alt text](components.png \"SOURCE\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###### Source: https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170214005357/en/ZestFinance-Introduces-Machine-Learning-Platform-Underwrite-Millennials"
   ]
