  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### *Landscape and Competition*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Credit underwriting is the core of every lending business but the traditional methods are labor instensive and with a significant data gathering burden for both the lender and borrower. The summary of what composes a good lending business has not yet changed but all companies in this domain are looking to achieve more efficiency and effectiveness in credit underwriting. \n",
    "\n",
    "While in the recent past a business or person needed to prove a solid financial track record to get credit, new data sources are becoming more reliable in such decision making processes. Innovations such as the integrations of APIs that give to the underwriter the ability to pull data from different sources is a major trend that has impacted the industry across the board. Other than credit bureaus and bank recors, data points gathered through lien searches, social networks, online transaction records and cloud based accounting systems are reaching the credit underwriters through these APIs and providing a closer look at the borrower. Data points on a borrower used to make a decision has increased in the industry overall, in ZEST AI specifically, the startup estimates to use over 10 times more data than the traditional methods its clients were using before. \n",
    "\n",
    "The scenario of the competition ZEST AI finds itself in is tricky to understand. While its clients can significantly increase profits while reducing risk by using ZAML, they can become its strongest competitor if they decide to put the money and time into it. Considering companies such as Rocket Mortgage, SoFi and Zillow that all have a very strong customer base, let alone banks, ZEST AI is forced to always have its AI model at the forefront of innovation and effectiveness. Otherwise, the ROI for its clients to create their own models would be something they would be willing to take the risk. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###### **Research Source:** https://lendingfront.com/blog/industry/underwriting-the-new-underwriting-technology-evaluating-innovations-in-data-use-and-credit-decisioning/"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Impact in the industry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![alt text](discover.png \"SOURCE\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Zest AI has already proved your point in the market with ZAML and its still only tapping into the credit underwritting market. Discover Financial Services, a leading direct banking and payments company with $90.5 billion dollars in loans, approached Zest in 2018 with the goal to improve its credit scoring to reduce risk and at the same time increase approvals and market share. After a succesful trial, Discover deployed its first credit under writing Machine Learning model into production in mid-2019. Zest capability allowed Discover to personalize the model to its preferences on the applicants' behaviors. For example, a history of discount store shopping would increase the applicant's chance of being approved for a personal loan while on the other hand calls from Skype or untracked phones would lower the chances. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In another example, Zest worked side by side with Akbank, the third largest private bank in Turkey. The bank had millons of potential younger customers with limited credit histories. Althouhg a credit track record was almost nonexistent, the bank had a gold mine of information about it's customers' spending habits and finances. \n",
    "According to Zest, they were able to reduce form 6 to 3 months Akbank's timeline to create, validate and test its models before going into production. The startup also boosted the models by adjusting them to look at 26 times more data than Akbank's linear regression models used before. Akbank deployed the machine learning models across five of it's product lines achieving 100% increase in \"no-credit history applicants\" approval rate and a 45% reduction in non-perfoming loans.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As credit underwriting is a fairly new application for AI, the industry still does not have standardized indicators to measure success. However as seen in both examples above, the two metrics that standed out are portfolio risk reduction and approval rate increase or market share. Zest AI models are showing to be significant superior than any tradional method currently used by its client and we are still to see any competitor with such capability. \n",
    "In the chart below, there is scientific evidence of how Zest's ensemble model produces the highest AUC, which is the % of times it ranks a good applicant higher than a bad applicant, when compared to other models."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
