   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Recommendations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As a standardized method that I use on my personal evaluations of each business, I focus on the three potential risks and weaknesses that a business model presents and how the business can mitigate them to continue to move forward and grow within the industry. These recommendations can include not only new products or services but also new procedures, how they can benifit from these changes and what additional development would be required. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The greatest potential risk for Zest AI business model is its own clients developing their in-house technology, which would make the costs for the startup's services unnecessary. A way out for this issue, would be if Zest were able to integrate its clients' databases so the models use not only the data that a single bank has but data sourced from all Zest's clients. It's unthinkable of banks sharing their data with competitors, but this would not be a raw data sharing, they would only use to better predict outcomes in their models leaving the actual information encrypted. Such solution would require an extensive work for data protection but on the long run it can be the tool to power Zest A's business."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Secondly, there is a very good chance that in the future the ZAML technology will become commoditized. As more and more institutions understand the power of AI they will incorporate such capabilities in its businesses and what Zest does today will become the new normal for credit underwriting. Zest AI will be obligated to incorporate and bundle new services in order to survive. The startup should look to new methods of underwriting, such as including cryptocurrencies in the credit rating industry. A practice that would revolutionize the industry but that will keep the startup in the forefront of innovation as crypto currencies earn more credibility every day. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Lastly, the access to personal data for credit underwriting. As the world understands how companies are using big data to explore new markets and profit, regulation will shed a light into the misuse or abuse of personal information by large tech companies. In the near future, there is a risk that such data Zest uses today will be confidential and would only be allowed to use under the individual consent. Altough fair and correct, such regulation present a serious threat to the AI developed by Zest with the limitation of data points input. The company needs to be ahead of the problem and develop predictive models that match the individual data with publicly available indicators to rate its credit, instead of comparing to other millions of individuals to then give a decision. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The chart below presents the benefit Zest AI's current technology provides to its clients. Such benefit has an extreme potential to be adopted industry wide and by mitigating the risks mentioned above Zest will position itself to be the main player in the adoption of AI for credit underwriting."
   ]
